// BT-2189: BUnit-level coverage for Beamtalk `implementorsOf:` — finds all
// classes that directly define a given selector. Backs System Browser-style
// navigation ("who else has this method?").
//
// Like `beamtalk_interface_test.bt`, this suite is limited to class-level
// introspection because the workspace singleton `Beamtalk` is not
// bootstrapped in the BUnit test context, and `BeamtalkInterface` is a
// `sealed typed Object subclass:` which cannot be instantiated.
//
// `implementorsOf:` is instance-only on the workspace singleton facade,
// matching Pharo's `SystemNavigation default allImplementorsOf:` shape.
// (Historical note: a class-side form was originally blocked by a
// self-deadlock when the iteration hit BeamtalkInterface itself —
// `c includesSelector:` would gen_server:call back into the running
// class gen_server. The BT-2189 __beamtalk_meta/0 fast path on
// classIncludesSelector/2 defused that concern for compiled stdlib
// classes, so the choice is now conventional rather than technical.)
//
// Behavioural tests for `implementorsOf:` (happy path, multi-implementor,
// no-implementor, stdlib participation) live in the E2E REPL-protocol suite
// at tests/repl-protocol/cases/workspace_native_api.btscript, which runs
// in workspace_mode and has the live `Beamtalk` singleton available.

TestCase subclass: BeamtalkImplementorsTest

  // --- selector existence ---
  testIncludesSelectorImplementorsOf =>
    self assert: (BeamtalkInterface includesSelector: #implementorsOf:)

  // --- composition primitives must be in place ---

  // The implementation calls self allClasses then filters by
  // includesSelector:. Both primitives have to be present.
  testCompositionPrimitivesPresent =>
    self assert: (BeamtalkInterface includesSelector: #allClasses)
    self assert: (Behaviour includesSelector: #includesSelector:)
